& [SourceSet] is the bounded research surface
  + [source_001] is Nordstrom, Proof Complexity and SAT Solving
    = link: https://jakobnordstrom.se/docs/publications/ProofComplexityChapter.pdf
    = use: explains SAT solvers as proof systems and reviews lower-bound phenomena for systems underlying SAT solving
  + [source_002] is Buss, Towards NP-P via Proof Complexity and Search
    = link: https://mathweb.ucsd.edu/~sbuss/ResearchWeb/lfcsSurvey/paper.pdf
    = use: surveys proof-complexity approaches to NP versus coNP and P versus NP
  + [source_003] is Pich and Santhanam, Towards P not equal NP from Extended Frege lower bounds
    = link: https://eccc.weizmann.ac.il/report/2023/199/download/
    = use: shows recent work connecting lower bounds for concrete proof systems to circuit lower-bound questions, preserving route difficulty
  + [source_004] is Dagstuhl Seminar 18051 Proof Complexity
    = link: https://www.dagstuhl.de/18051
    = use: summarizes active proof-complexity directions and the importance of lower bounds for bounded-depth Frege and beyond
  + [source_005] is Cornell Proof Complexity notes
    = link: https://www.cs.cornell.edu/~sabhar/publications/iaspcmi-proofcomplexity00.pdf
    = use: records the Cook-Reckhow frame relating polynomially bounded proof systems to NP versus coNP

& [ResearchFindings] is the theorem-boundary result
  + [finding_001] is proof systems are the correct language for unsat certificates
    = meaning: the P equals NP side must supply polynomial proof size or simulation power in a specified system
  + [finding_002] is many SAT-relevant systems have known hard instances or lower-bound programs
    = meaning: resolution, cutting planes, polynomial calculus, and related systems do not provide universal polynomial refutations in the checked frame
  + [finding_003] is stronger systems shift rather than remove the burden
    = meaning: Frege and extended Frege connect to major open lower-bound questions rather than settling certificate power
  + [finding_004] is a universal polynomial-refutation theorem would be a major collapse
    = meaning: no admitted source supplies such a theorem for all SAT/3-SAT
  + [finding_005] is informal P equals NP uploads are not authority
    = meaning: broad solution claims require independent accepted validation and are outside this research record

